         <div>
            <head>17.11.1882 Freitag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49069">Hamburg</placeName>. November 17. 1882
               Friday.</p>
            <p> Skated before breakfast. Ice pretty safe. Heavy fall of snow. We made a great many
               slides this morning at school. The ice not good in the afternoon. At about 5.45 there
               was a grand aurora torealis; and the snow was perfectly red with the glare. But it
               was cloudy so that we only saw the glare and at first thought it was a fire. Drove
                  <persName key="1178">Henny</persName> to a party in the evening, on the sledge and
               was driven part of the way home by <persName key="1156">Robert</persName> and
                  <persName key="1157">Martin</persName>
               <note type="reg">beide Blümer</note>.</p>
         </div>
